Okay, I am ready. I will be going from top to bottom. I will give everyone a number of how lit I feel they are

Dorothy: Not as active at times which can of course be attributed to meta, but it could also be a guise under which a wolf could keep low-profile. That said, whenever she did come on she put on her thinking cap and really seemed to have a villagery mindset in trying to solve who is who. All her lynch choices were well thought out, but she could also easily sway opinions by doing that. Other than that it doesn't seem like she's done anything particularly wolfy to me. 6.5/10

Hunk: I can't get a good enough read on him due to slightly lesser activity, but he hasn't done anything particularly wolfy either; he is somewhat in the middle. BUT the way they were happy about lynching ECG yesterday which I am very sure was a wolf gives them brownie points; yes I know that can be faked, but my gut feels tell me the reaction was geniuine and therefore I think Hunk is most probably a villager. 9/10

AuntieEm: Now this is a tough one. At first I had lit vibes from her just from the way she approached the game and discussed all the options, but then I noticed her odd way of voting which seemed like she was avoiding having to come up with a proper reason to vote so just voted wherever; I am specifically talking about D3 when we lynched Gulch. She left her vote on Zeke, said it was a mistake, and then just left it there...in a setup where all of us must carefully decide whom to lynch. Yes it was early but still, I did not like the carefree approach in just leaving a vote like that. It seemed wolfy to me for a second. That being said, she has afterwards been a lot more thorough in the way she's been voting, but that might have been because I called her out on it. I could be looking into it too much, who knows. She also hasn't been as active, which again either meta or a wolf keeping low-profile, but whenever she came on she had some impact. Her voting against ECG does give her lit points, but as Toto said that could have been staged to make her look a lot more lit. With all being said, the way she's been playing ostensibly seems villagery, but my gut feels like there is something more behind her. 5.5/10

Toto: The player that keeps coming on and off my list of susses. His aggressive demeanor, or bluntness as he likes to put it, can come off as wolfish, especially whenever he got sussed, but his approach in solving the game tells me the COMPLETE opposite. He's trying really hard to solve the game in a manner I find it hard to imagine a wolf doing, so he is either a very good wolf or just a villager. I have troubles seeing him as a wolf, even though he is suspicious at times. He'd be 5/10 but my gut tells me he is 8/10. Should I trust my gut I do not know.

Marvel: Ah, Witch vs Marvel again. I was very sure of Witch when we lynched her but the more I read the archives the more I doubt myself. One thing that my gut really dislikes whenever I read your words is how much of a middle-man you are in every discussion. You seem like you are trying to solve the game as well, but almost whenever you give your opinions you write them in such a clever way that appears as if you are giving a thorough opinion, but is essentially one big "lol idk" hidden behind a wall of text. You'd be a great politician you know. I can see both a villager and a wolf doing that, but it's a great wolf strat to make yourself seem like you're engaging in discussion without actually contributing. Another thing that particularly stood out to me was when you said "I was gonna go with Uncle and vote Toto, but I just don't see it. Sorry guys.". Why follow me exactly? Because I was sort of the "village leader"? A wolf cuddling up to the most talkative villager in order to be on his good side is one wolf strat I know oh all too well and that you have done well with me if you are a wolf. Also, I know I said I won't go hard on you for making mistakes on how the TR works, but I also can't just forget it still...I am very open to having been wrong about Witch and if I am I hope she forgives my folly. With everything said and including my gut feels on this, I give you a 4/10

Zeke: You are very very tough to read due to lesser activity (again, low-profile wolf, or meta busy villager?). Your way of voting at times seemed weird to me, like on d3 when you voted no trial...it might be just me but voting no trial in THIS setup is so not a villager thing to do. In other days whenever you did come on you never knew where to vote nor did it seem like you were actually trying much to figure that out but would rather follow the villagers top vote. If I also go by process of elimination you are one my top votes as well. 4/10, guts included

These are my views. I put a small sentence about my feelings at first. Not because I want to judge people on whether I do or don’t think they’re nice. But because I am aware that not vibing with someone can make them more sus to you, while I tend to overlook someone if they are really fun to have in the game. So it’s to take into account my own confirmation bias. 
I also want to say that I stand by what I said yesterday, I don’t really trust anyone. I have difficulty just working with what people say. Only thing I am really sure about is FakeEmerald.

Dorothy: Friendly but a bit absent. Was against the PR claim, saying it helps wolves more than villagers. Suggested lynching on D2. Fought Emerald’s attack on Lollipop on D3. Says she has notes on everyones susses on D3 –.are they shown? But doesn’t explain the susses herself during the earlier days.
Did some villager moves, did some weird things. 
Little sus.

Hunk: Comes across a bit chaotic sometimes, cares about making the game enjoyable for all. Agreed with the PR claim, stating he needed information. I don’t always follow his conversation. I don’t think his reasoning for FakeEmerald was correct, but his joy at catching a wolf comes across as true villager joy to me.
Likely villager.

Toto: Gets too aggressive for my taste, this puts me off. Had really good reasons against a PR claim before a tarot read, but was otherwise silent a lot of the time. His questions or proposals sometimes mirror things that were said not so long ago before his arrival. Can be that he doesn’t read back before he writes himself, but it also looks like a wolf that wants to be seen as an active participant while not really doing much. I think he can reason quite well when he’s talking about possible motives, but I would have expected more help with actually catching wolves from a strategic person such as him. I feel like he is using his talents more to bring chaos instead of making things more clear.
In the first half of the week he was quite relaxed and explaining his preferences calmly. His tone and attitude shifted a lot as soon as he was named as a possible sus.
I also found it quite odd that he went after Winkie so hard, then he claimed he didn’t sus Winkie last evening and then after Winkie died he was ready at first thing in the morning to make sure everyone knew that it was obvious that a Winkie kill wouldn’t be him.
I also found it odd that Toto doubted the conclusion of FakeEmerald that much, I think it was pretty obvious.
He’s wolving in a way that I wouldn’t expect him to do, but perhaps that’s the double bluff.
Likely wolf. 

Marvel: Entertaining player who has a varying pattern of activity. Agreed with the PR claim. Didn’t want to lynch on D2. I really want to assume Witch was the right choice, it didn’t feel like it at the time if I am honest. However, seeing as Marvel wasn’t there at D1. I think the weird questions could be because he was surprised that the game had started already and he didn’t read into the setup properly before talking. I don’t think it’s likely that Marvel is together with Toto, so that drives me to the assumption that Witch was the right one and Marvel is the true PR. If Toto is lit, Marvel might be a problem.
If Toto is wolf, Marvel is lit.

Henry: Very active and enjoyable player. Started the PR plan, which didn’t make sense to me. Takes the blame, but still said that most were in favor while that wasn’t true. I feel like Henry steered people in a certain direction with voting in the early days, not naming 1 person but giving a few options. So he could be sure that a villager was lynched while not being the one to go for someone personally. He said he didn’t feel like Gulch was wolf afterwards, but he did say Monkey was his first choice and Gulch second.I feel like Henry is trying to take the blame partly to seem reliable and then hoping we won’t read too much into the part he is trying to keep hidden.
He is either still alive because he is a wolf or because the wolves like him doing their work for them. 

Zeke: This is a wild card for me, I like him but I cannot get a read on him. What speaks in favour of him is that Lolli and Witch both found him sus. 
I don’t know.

That said, whenever she did come on she put on her thinking cap and really seemed to have a villagery mindset in trying to solve who is who. All her lynch choices were well thought out, but she could also easily sway opinions by doing that. Other than that it doesn't seem like she's done anything particularly wolfy to me. 6.5/10 ## Hunk I can't get a good enough read on him due to slightly lesser activity, but he hasn't done anything particularly wolfy either; he is somewhat in the middle. BUT the way they were happy about lynching ECG yesterday which I am very sure was a wolf gives them brownie points; yes I know that can be faked, but my gut feels tell me the reaction was geniuine and therefore I think Hunk is most probably a villager. 9/10 ## AuntieEm Now this is a tough one. At first I had lit vibes from her just from the way she approached the game and discussed all the options, but then I noticed her odd way of voting which seemed like she was avoiding having to come up with a proper reason to vote so just voted wherever; I am specifically talking about D3 when we lynched Gulch. She left her vote on Zeke, said it was a mistake, and then just left it there...in a setup where all of us must carefully decide whom to lynch. Yes it was early but still, I did not like the carefree approach in just leaving a vote like that. It seemed wolfy to me for a second. That being said, she has afterwards been a lot more thorough in the way she's been voting, but that might have been because I called her out on it. I could be looking into it too much, who knows. She also hasn't been as active, which again either meta or a wolf keeping low-profile, but whenever she came on she had some impact. Her voting against ECG does give her lit points, but as Toto said that could have been staged to make her look a lot more lit. With all being said, the way she's been playing ostensibly seems villagery, but my gut feels like there is something more behind her. 5.5/10 ## Toto The player that keeps coming on and off my list of susses. His aggressive demeanor, or bluntness as he likes to put it, can come off as wolfish, especially whenever he got sussed, but his approach in solving the game tells me the COMPLETE opposite. He's trying really hard to solve the game in a manner I find it hard to imagine a wolf doing. I have troubles seeing him as a wolf, even though he is suspicious at times. He'd be 5/10 but my gut tells me he is 8/10. Should I trust my gut I do not know. ## Marvel Ah, Witch vs Marvel again. I was very sure of Witch when we lynched her but the more I read the archives the more I doubt myself. One thing that my gut really dislikes whenever I read your words is how much of a middle-man you are in every discussion. You seem like you are trying to solve the game as well, but almost whenever you give your opinions you write them in such a clever way that appears as if you are giving a thorough opinion, but is essentially one big "lol idk" hidden behind a wall of text. You'd be a great politician you know. I can see both a villager and a wolf doing that, but it's a great wolf strat to make yourself seem like you're engaging in discussion without actually contributing. Another thing that particularly stood out to me was when you said "I was gonna go with Uncle and vote Toto, but I just don't see it. Sorry guys.". Why follow me exactly? Because I was sort of the "village leader"? A wolf cuddling up to the most talkative villager in order to be on his good side is one wolf strat I know oh all too well and that you have done well with me if you are a wolf. Also, I know I said I won't go hard on you for making mistakes on how the TR works, but I also can't just forget it still...I am very open to having been wrong about Witch and if I am I hope she forgives my folly. With everything said and including my gut feels on this, I give you a 3/10 ## Zeke You are very very tough to read due to lesser activity (again, low-profile wolf, or meta busy villager?). Your way of voting at times seemed weird to me, like on d3 when you voted no trial...it might be just me but voting no trial in THIS setup is so not a villager thing to do. In other days whenever you did come on you never knew where to vote nor did it seem like you were actually trying much to figure that out but would rather follow the villagers top vote. ~~If I also go by process of elimination you are one my top votes as well. 4/10, guts included~~ CHANGE OF OPINION: His reaction today on witch dying tells me he is NOT a wolf, but the person that was not surprised was EM, and EM is rather adamant on not voting Marvel...7/10 for Zeke. If I am correct the only possible team I see is: ### **EM, DOROTHY and MARVEL**
